You need to take input until your exit condition is satisfied (score == -1). And if your validation condition is violated (score &lt; -1 or score &gt; 100) you should prompt the user again for input. 

Simplest way is to use a do-while loop and add a if-statement for validation:
```
int score = 0;
do {
        System.out.printf(&quot;Enter a score (0 too 100, -1 to quit #%d:)&quot;, studentCount);
        score = stdin.nextInt();         
        if (score &gt; 100 || score &lt; -1) {
            System.out.println(&quot;Illegal Score Try Again&quot;);
            continue;
        }
        studentCount++;
        total += score;
} while (score != -1);
```

P.S: You are not adding score to the running total in your loop. Added that.

